13. Production Hardening Layer (LangGraph State Machine + Reliability System)
This section defines the missing execution-grade layer required to convert the orchestration design into a stable, debuggable system.
13.1 Core State Machine Model (LangGraph)
The system is formalized as a directed state graph with strict transition rules.
Primary Nodes

INTAKE_NODE
   * Input validation

   * Task normalization

   * Risk pre-assessment (sanity check)

PLANNER_NODE
   * Generates structured JSON plan

   * Assigns risk score

   * Defines tool dependencies

EXECUTOR_NODE
   * Executes steps sequentially or via tool calls

   * Produces artifacts (code, queries, scripts)

CRITIC_NODE (Fast / Deep Tiered)
   * Validates outputs against schema + constraints

   * Produces structured review only (no freeform planning)

REPAIR_NODE
   * Applies critic feedback

   * Limited to max 2 iterations per cycle

REPLAN_NODE
   * Triggered after repair failure threshold

   * Regenerates full plan from latest checkpoint

TOOL_EXECUTION_NODE
   * Executes external tools (DB, Git, Blender, APEX, filesystem)

   * Returns standardized tool schema

FINALIZATION_NODE
   * Aggregates outputs

   * Commits checkpoints

   * Stores episodic memory record

13.2 State Transition Rules
Transitions are deterministic and governed by risk + validation outcomes.
Core transitions:

INTAKE → PLANNER
PLANNER → EXECUTOR
EXECUTOR → CRITIC
CRITIC → FINALIZATION (if success)
CRITIC → REPAIR (if failure ≤ 2 cycles)
REPAIR → CRITIC
CRITIC → REPLAN (if failure ≥ 3 cycles)
REPLAN → PLANNER
EXECUTOR → TOOL_EXECUTION (when external dependency required)
TOOL_EXECUTION → EXECUTOR (return loop)
13.3 Failure Model & Deterministic Recovery
All failures must map to a structured taxonomy:

schema_mismatch
logic_error
tool_failure
env_failure
timeout
permission_error
Recovery Rules:

schema_mismatch → JSON repair pass (fast model) → retry node
logic_error → CRITIC_NODE review + REPAIR
tool_failure → retry tool or switch execution path
env_failure → halt + escalate to FINALIZATION with error state
timeout → checkpoint rollback + re-execute last valid node
13.4 Tool Contract Test Suite (Mandatory)
Every tool must pass deterministic validation before integration.
Test Requirements:

input schema validation (strict typing)
output schema compliance
failure mode simulation
checkpoint integrity verification
Example test categories:

PL/SQL query execution correctness
